body.name: KEDIERS PC Case - ATX Mid Tower Tempered Glass Gaming Computer Open Frame Case with 7 ARGB Fans
body.stockDetail: Only 10 left in stock - order soon.
features: [Powerful cooling system]-- KEDIERS gaming computer case is pre-installed with 7 RGB dual light ring LED fans: 3 x front, 2 x top,2 x side; The open design can keep the GPU continuously low，making your computer run more smoothly.

[2 tempered glass panels]-- KEDIERS 570 gaming case is equipped with 2 * 4mm thick translucent tempered glass, which can clearly see the RGB lighting, which can protect and display all the components in the building, and bring better to players Game experience.

[Synchronizable RGB Lighting via Motherboard]-- It allows you to control fan lighting with 5V-3PIN addressable RGB motherboards. Compatible with motherboard software includes US aura Sync,MSI Mystic Light Sync, etc.
[I/O Panel]-- 2 x USB3.0 Port, 1 x USB2.0 Port, 1 x HD Audio, RGB Button, Power Button.

[Remarkable Expansion]-- This decent ATX Mid Tower Gaming Computer Case supports motherboards up to ATX, Micro-ATX, Mini-ITX; Back Bays: 1x 3.5'' HDD's and 3 x 2.5'' SSD's. Suitable for official 3090, 3080, 3060 GPU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Soo many fans! I love how this keeps max airflow through my PC. I did have to re-mount the top fans to the bottom of the case to fit in the liquid cooler system. I really wished it came with fans mounted to the bottom by default. Overall, I love the way my PC looks and feels!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect case for me
reviews.reviewText: Very stylish, but open case to get a lot of air flow. Love that it came with many fans pre installed and a fan module/remote. Extremely sturdy structure, a bit heavy but better quality then most. Good amount of diy ARGB options from remote itself. Fits for almost any build you want to do, I have a x570 elite mobo and a EVGA 3070ti in mine with extra clearance for the GPU only! The extended mobo’s probably won’t fit in this case unless you have a short psu

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars The case I really nice, and stays incredibly cool but..
reviews.reviewText: This was the first open design case I've ever messed with. The assembly process can be a bit of a headache and not newbie friendly to those just getting into pc building.Pros:The case looks amazing especially with the fan lights, the size of this case is also at a perfect middle ground with it being pretty compact for an ATX mid tower but having an pretty good amount of space to work with inside.Air flow is by far the best thing about this case. It comes with 7 case fans, on top of my chromamax and 3070 fans the case stays impressively cool 99% of the time even when stress testing.One last thing I loved about this case is the option to expand the glass sides to make some more room. I have a noctua chromamax installed and that boy is a heck heckin beast. It fit perfectly with just about an inch of space left so i didnt need the extended brackets for the glass panel but it's really neat to have that option.Cons:The case has little to no room for HDD or SDD drives, make sure your mobo has slots for m.2s cause it'll be far less of a headache just using them instead.The two fans on the front glass panel are both a good and bad thing here, the good thing is they actually pull a decent amount of air in considering they're centimeters from the glass panel. The bad thing is in order to even reach or install your psu you're gonna have to pull those fans out. Not a huge issue but for someone who's new to building and is somewhat impatient its not a good thing.Last but not least is structure. The case by itself with both panels removed is weak. Barely putting pressure on it with cause the back to give and break.The case is truly nice, and probably one of my most favorite cases I've owned up to this point, the only reason I'm giving 3 stars is because the packaging was damaged, box and Styrofoam. And I'm missing a few parts that were supposed to come with it, specifically the two trays for drives. Again not a big deal but still, someone messed up somewhere.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great case, hard cable management
reviews.reviewText: Great case all around came with USB 3.0 and all fans and power/LED switches connected, easy design to find where everything should go, managing the cables is a bit tricky due to such an open design. The ONE and ONLY issue I had with the case was a top fan had a slight wobble to it which created a clicking sound when running, simple fix just pushed it up and down and got the wobble out of it, other than that everything went smooth and worked as it should, very quiet as well! Great bang for your buck. 9.75/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Poor quality control with good cooling and rgb! !
reviews.reviewText: Garbage, cheap materials scew holes strip easy had to re-thread 6 of them already. If you like loud fans this is the case for you, I replaced them with corsair ones. Just the feel of the power button is enough to show the quality of the item, it works sometimes. Not for a first time builder as you'll have no guidance or instructions, also note that my frame was not aligned/even , I had to remove the rivets and aline them so the MOBO would sit on properly. 3 out of 10 recommend $99 is a better price for this case.NOTES : will not fit a radiator larger than 240mmSsd and hdd must be installed before mobo to avoid issuesRgb is not pretty good if you keep stock fans

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good looking case, especially for the price and having fans included.
reviews.reviewText: It's a good looking case and it's great that it comes with fans... It'd be even better if they all worked. After building the computer, everything worked and looked good, but a singular fan doesn't seem to want to spin. I've had the case for a couple days. The, problem could possibly lay with me, but I've checked for debrie, as well as any other obstructions. Overall, it's worth the chance, my case seems like a few of a dozen

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It fits a 4090 Rog Strix !!!.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Very unique and compact mid tower gaming case. Not Much room for cable management, overall case is nice. Surprisingly fits a 4090 video card barely probably 1-2 mm from touching the front fan shroud. Mounted my 240 water cooler Asus Rog Ryujin II AIO on the top in a push pull configuration.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE THIS CASE
reviews.reviewText: I bought this case in 2020. It's 2022 and this things is still going strong. No issues with the build, and the style is eye catching. I get compliments on it all the time. the RGB fans have a huge range of styles that can be selected. Not to mention there is more than enough space for all of your components, even the biggest graphics cards! HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT.

Bought this for my husband who has been searching for a good ATX case that will accommodate his massive motherboard. He was so thrilled with this case not only is it the perfect size but it comes with so many RGB fans included which saved us from having to buy those separately. The case is beautiful and streamlined, large but not bulky. The price is well worth it for the quality and extra fans and components that were included. 10/10 recommend!!

Elle est parfaite visuellementMais pour le prix je m’aurais attendu a une meilleure qualité de matérielLes weld spot sont apparent de l’extérieur les défauts paraissent de près avec la couleur noir et les fans avant ne sont pas protégés. Complètement à découvert. La qualité des port usb sont très moyens. La qualité des boutons aussi.

Me gustó mucho el diseño, estoy bastante conforme con los ventiladores ya que se les puede cambiar el color y las velocidades, además incluye 5 filtros/protectores para que se los pongas a los ventiladores de arriba y a los frontales. Le puse 4 estrellas porque los tornillos de los ventiladores venían muy apretados, dos se me barrieron y uno de los orificios se rompió (tuve mucho cuidado pero aun así). También me costó ponerle los tornillos de la placa madre. Y por último aunque no se que tan importante sea cuando lo abrí venía el gabinete cubierto de polvo
I really like the looks of this case alot came exactly as shown looks even better out of the box cant wait to build it.

It looks really cool, and that's what I wanted.I read the bad reviews about the install, and they are right.I have a wide ass double rad that took a few hours to figure out the placing for. It's an open small ass case, everything is compact, but it looks cool!Cons: The USBs in the front are super tight, lost a USB in one of them.The Fans won't really sync to Aura, they are three pins instead of the 4 pin rgb headers. You can still change it with the button on the bottom and the remote so not a deal breaker.
